claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A photograph of the bottom of a clinical document page showing the tail end of a paragraph reporting influenza vaccine effectiveness percentages against RT-PCR–confirmed ILI in different age groups, followed by the start of another paragraph referencing a 2019 editorial by Flannery and Fry, and a page footer with the number 5138. The excerpt discusses vaccine effectiveness data and an editorial commentary but contains no information about Flublok’s antigenic match with WHO- or FDA-selected flu strains, so it does not support the claim. Note: None
